President Uhuru Kenyatta has so far held two meetings at Sagana State Lodge in Nyeri County. Insiders of the meeting have on record said the gatherings aimed at shaping the political direction of the Mt Kenya region. Uhuru after a fall-out with his deputy William Ruto is keen on directing the Mt Kenya region on a political path he deems fit for the region. He is also expected to hold Sagana three meetings soon where sources say he will reveal what went wrong between him and the DP.